{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idb9c5dc3d-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s4043"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4043"},"text":"§ 4043.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Acceptance of gifts and bequests to the Commissary Funds, Federal Prisons","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Attorney General may accept gifts or bequests of money for credit to the “Commissary Funds, Federal Prisons”. A gift or bequest under this section is a gift or bequest to or for the use of the United States under the Internal Revenue Code of 1986 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t26/s1"},"text":"26 U.S.C. 1","children":[],"tail":" et seq.)."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idb9c5dc3e-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/258/s2/d/4/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–258, § 2(d)(4)(B)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1982-09-13"},"text":"Sept. 13, 1982","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/96/1059"},"text":"96 Stat. 1059","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/514/s2"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–514, § 2","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1986-10-22"},"text":"Oct. 22, 1986","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/100/2095"},"text":"100 Stat. 2095","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idb9c5dc3f-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"idb9c5dc40-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:table","attrib":{"width":"50%","id":"idb9c5dc41-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:colgroup","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[